Ok I'm done with self reflection :)

-that inner child or inner teenager. You can still live your childhood. Watch cartoons early morning. Go to Disneyland. Go to build a bear. Just because you're older doesn't mean you have to "act like an adult". Do what you need to heal yourself aside form what society says.

Here's the thing- age is just a number. You've been alive for this many years but that doesn't mean you suddenly cant do things. Remake a prom for you and your friends. Relive those fashion trends you didn't get to experience. Do what you need to so you can soothe-

You're stuck on the thought that trauma has taken so many years from you that you're 10 years older, and you never got to actually experience your childhood or teenage years because you were just trying to survive.

You're older than your mind is. Your body is 25 but mentally, you're starting at 16 or 17. Your brain is finally ready to let you live but it won't let you catch up.. so you get confused. And scared. Your body is aging faster than your brain is ready for and now...

So once you finally get help, get diagnosed and are finally going to therapy or on meds, you come back to reality- even for a moment. You're not thinking of ending it as much, you're not hoping for tomorrow to come cause today is so painful, you're calm... And that's when it hits

It sucks when you grow up in trauma, all your years go by so quick. You're disassociating and time has no meaning because you always thought of ending it due to it all being too much for one young human being to take.
